&lt;h2&gt;


Multiple queries in a single component
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rendering via JSX allows working with multiple queries in a single component.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suppose each item references a tag dictionary via &lt;code&gt;tagId&lt;/code&gt;, and we need to display the tag title.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this case, you can nest &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;SwitchQuery /&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; elements within each other. The order in which responses are received doesnâ€™t matter, as all states are accounted for at every level.&lt;br&gt;
