&lt;h2&gt;


Conclusion
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One might argue that all the examples above are flawed and it would be better to move everything into separate components. This is a perfectly valid stance and you could even use &lt;code&gt;useSuspenseQuery&lt;/code&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, in this case, implementation of a single interface block would be spread across multiple components and files, which would also need to be named.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe that &lt;code&gt;@tanstack/react-query&lt;/code&gt; blurs established patterns by making the request an integral part of the views, which aligns with the final result. The libraryâ€™s declarative API is perfectly complemented by the declarative nature of JSX.&lt;/p&gt;

