&lt;p&gt;Form handling is one of those core skills every developer must eventually master. Whether youâ€™re building login pages, search bars, dashboards, admin portals, or complex data-entry tools, &lt;strong&gt;forms power user interaction&lt;/strong&gt;. Todayâ€™s topic â€” &lt;strong&gt;Form Handling + TypeScript&lt;/strong&gt; â€” is about making this experience smoother, safer, and more predictable.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


What Exactly &lt;em&gt;Is&lt;/em&gt; Form Handling?
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Form handling is simply the process of:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collecting data from form fields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keeping track of what the user types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validating user input&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Submitting this data to a server or using it within the app&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Without proper form handling, apps break, data becomes unreliable, and the user experience suffers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In short:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
ðŸ‘‰ &lt;em&gt;Form handling ensures your UI and your data stay in sync.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h2&gt;


Controlled vs Uncontrolled Forms: Whatâ€™s the Difference?
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;React gives us &lt;strong&gt;two ways&lt;/strong&gt; to handle form data. Both work â€” but for different reasons.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;


âœ” Controlled Forms
&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;controlled input&lt;/strong&gt; is fully managed by React state.&lt;br&gt;
Whatever you type in the input goes into the state, and the state feeds the inputâ€™s value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pros:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full UI control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Easy validation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;State is always the source of truth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perfect with TypeScript since everything is typed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cons:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Slightly more boilerplate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;More re-renders if not optimized&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;


Example:
&lt;/h4&gt;


